This document is a guide on how to build ReVanced Extended using the RVX Manager. 2. To use the RVX Manager, the following conditions must be met: Common 0. If you are preparing to install in ROOT environment, follow the method below 1. Check the README.md of revanced-patches for supported YouTube versions 2. Download the supported version of YouTube / YouTube Music from APKMirror. 3. Download RVX Manager from the github and install it on your device 4. Launch RVX Manager and Open [Settings] > [Sources] 5. Restart the application (Important) 6. Open [Patcher] then click Select an application. 7. Click the Storage button and select the YouTube APK that you downloaded from APKMirror 8. Click Selected patches and include or exclude the patches you want NON-ROOT environment ROOT environment Method 4. Using Revancify (Android termux) About Revancify How to install Revancify for the first time Usage Guide with screenshots Options Information about the patch Options: Information about the patch YouTube YouTube Music Patches that need to be included or excluded depending on the situation If you want the ROOT version: Using CLI: -e microg-support If you want a Revancify Red Icon: Using CLI: -e custom-branding-icon-mmt -i custom-branding-icon-revancify-red -e custom-branding-icon-revancify-blue If you want a Revancify Blue Icon: Using CLI: -e custom-branding-icon-mmt -e custom-branding-icon-revancify-red -i custom-branding-icon-revancify-blue If you want a MMT Icon: Using CLI: -i custom-branding-icon-mmt -e custom-branding-icon-revancify-red -e custom-branding-icon-revancify-blue If you want the Original YouTube Icon: Using CLI: -e custom-branding-icon-mmt -e custom-branding-icon-revancify-red -e custom-branding-icon-revancify-blue If you want a Custom App Name: Using CLI: -i custom-branding-youtube-name -i custom-branding-music-name If you want the Original App Name: Using CLI: -e custom-branding-youtube-name -e custom-branding-music-name If you want Stock YouTube Theme: Using CLI: -e theme -e materialyou If you want Only Black Theme: Using CLI: -i theme -e materialyou If you want MaterialYou Theme (Only for Android 12+): Using CLI: -e theme -i materialyou If you want MaterialYou Theme (Only for Android 12+) + Black Theme: Using CLI: -i theme -i materialyou If you want Force Premium Header: Using CLI: -i force-premium-heading Clone this wiki locally Information 1. This document is a guide on how to build ReVanced Extended using the RVX Manager. 2. To use the RVX Manager, the following conditions must be met: Your device must use the arm64-v8a architecture. Your device must be running Android 8.0+ Common 0. If you are preparing to install in ROOT environment, follow the method below remove all YouTube related modules remove directories: /data/adb/service.d, /data/adb/post-fs-data.d, /data/adb/revanced reboot device 1. Check the README.md of revanced-patches for supported YouTube versions â» For YouTube Music, all versions are supportedâ 2. Download the supported version of YouTube / YouTube Music from APKMirror. â» You must download the nodpi version. 3. Download RVX Manager from the github and install it on your device 4. Launch RVX Manager and Open [Settings] > [Sources] Setting value Patches organization YT-Advanced Patches source ReX-patches Integrations organization YT-Advanced Integrations source ReX-integrations 5. Restart the application (Important) 6. Open [Patcher] then click Select an application. 7. Click the Storage button and select the YouTube APK that you downloaded from APKMirror 8. Click Selected patches and include or exclude the patches you want If you don't know what to decide, just click the Default button When selected, click the Done button â» Read this document for a list of patches you can include or exclude. â» Read this document to see a screenshot of each patch NON-ROOT environment When patching, please include the following patches MicroG Support ROOT environment When patching, please exclude the following patches MicroG Support I recommend installing the Detach Magisk module after patching. â» Detach Magisk module prevents automatic updates by Google Playstore.
